    return -(-32*x**3 - 12*x**2 + 56*x + 24)

Solving a Linear System¶

In [51]:
# Create some random system to solve
N = 2
A = np.random.normal(size=(N,N)) + np.identity(N)
b = np.random.rand(N)
print(A)
print(b)

[[-0.17222299 -0.24336812]
 [-1.58115952  0.11011132]]
[0.09377942 0.31695759]
In [52]:
def SquaredResid(x):
    return np.sum((A@x-b)**2)
In [53]:
def gradSquaredResid(x):
    return A.T @ (A@x-b)
In [54]:
# Initial guess
x0 = np.zeros(N)
In [55]:
# Gradient descent
iters = 300
x = x0
kappa = 0.04
xh = [x[0]]
yh = [x[1]]
zh = [SquaredResid(x)]
for iter in range(iters):
    x -= kappa * gradSquaredResid(x)
    xh.append(x[0])
    yh.append(x[1])
    zh.append(SquaredResid(x))
In [56]:
# Our apprximate solution
print(x)

[-0.21060007 -0.11979582]
In [57]:
# The actual solution
xs = np.linalg.solve(A,b)
print(xs)

[-0.21661858 -0.23204648]
In [58]:
nx = 20
ny = nx
rge = 1
xs = np.linspace(-rge, rge, nx)
ys = np.linspace(-rge, rge, ny)
X,Y = np.meshgrid(xs, ys)
Z = np.zeros(np.shape(X))
for xi in range(nx):
    for yi in range(ny):
        Z[xi,yi] = SquaredResid(np.array([X[xi,yi], Y[xi,yi]]))
